CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 20, 1969, pg. 15 reads: "The First Black Brownie Troop to be established in Hazelwood, Glenwood and Glen-Hazel area, was recently set up at the St. John Baptist Church, Hazelwood. The proud little girls are pictured with their leader.  From left: Patricia Hill, leader; Patricia Craig, Toni Hill, Cheryl Richardson, Judy Hoston, Marion Kelly, Sheron Houser, Melvia Jones, Marshelle Bennett, Debbie McNary, Adrian Brown, Lisa Brown, Doreen Jones, Michelle St. Julien, and in rear, Mrs. Eloise Stanford and Mrs. Julia Bennett.
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Brownie troop, left to right, Patricia Hill, leader; Patricia Craig, Toni Hill, Cheryl Richardson, Judy Hoston, Marion Kelly, Sheron Houser, Melvia Jones, Marshelle Bennett, Debbie McNary, Adrian Brown, Lisa Brown, Doreen Jones, Michelle St. Julien, and in rear, Eloise Stanford and Julia Bennett, gathered in room of St. John Baptist Church
